1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,760
This is MakeYour, one iPhone app

2
00:00:02,760 --> 00:00:05,990
where GPT-5.6 creates
the tiny apps you need.

3
00:00:06,100 --> 00:00:08,550
My Apps keeps every creation.

4
00:00:08,650 --> 00:00:11,450
Builder is where you create
or change them.

5
00:00:11,550 --> 00:00:16,450
AI Key connects your own OpenAI key
and GPT-5.6.

6
00:00:16,550 --> 00:00:20,400
Together, they become one home
for your personal tiny apps.

7
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,400
Let's create one.

8
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:25,900
I tap New App and ask for
a daily focus checklist

9
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:28,200
with three tasks and a local reminder.

10
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:32,900
GPT-5.6 turns that prompt into
a validated, versioned app,

11
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:35,650
and MakeYour opens
the working native interface.

12
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:37,200
This is not a mockup.
I can use it immediately.

13
00:00:37,900 --> 00:00:40,200
A useful app should also feel like yours.

14
00:00:40,650 --> 00:00:42,800
I complete a task, return to Builder,

15
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:46,000
and ask for a calm green design
with a short evening reflection.

16
00:00:46,700 --> 00:00:50,400
GPT-5.6 creates Version 3
with a new style and a new feature,

17
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:53,500
while my completed task is still there.

18
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:56,650
The app changes with me,
without starting over.

19
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:59,300
Back in My Apps, Daily Focus

20
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:01,300
is only one of many.

21
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:04,400
I can switch to a travel budget
converter,

22
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:06,950
live currency alerts,
or a private food journal.

23
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:10,700
Every tiny app can have
its own interface, capabilities, and data,

24
00:01:10,700 --> 00:01:14,200
while they all live inside MakeYour.

25
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:16,100
No new Xcode project.

26
00:01:16,300 --> 00:01:17,900
No separate build pipeline.

27
00:01:18,100 --> 00:01:19,750
No starting from scratch.

28
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:23,600
Codex helped us build and test
the schema, validator,

29
00:01:23,650 --> 00:01:27,950
safety boundary, and native SwiftUI
runtime that make this possible.

30
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:31,100
The next tiny app you need
is one prompt away.

31
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:32,200
One app.

32
00:01:32,550 --> 00:01:33,750
Your tiny apps.

33
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:34,850
Make yours.
